---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Apply" description="Apply for the Oxford LLMs Summer School 2025.">
  <div class="container container--content">

    <div class="page-header">
      <p class="section-label">Apply</p>
      <h1 class="page-header__title">Apply for Oxford LLMs 2025</h1>
      <p class="page-header__desc">
        Applications for the September 2025 summer school open on April 10.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Who Should Apply</h2>
      <p>
        If you're an early career researcher — PhD student, postdoc, or advanced master's
        student — this workshop is for you. The programme is designed for social scientists
        who want to integrate LLMs into their research: political scientists, sociologists,
        historians, economists, and adjacent fields.
      </p>

      <h2>What You'll Get</h2>
      <p>
        Five days of lectures on LLM architecture and methods, hands-on coding sessions,
        a collaborative research project with potential for publication, and direct access
        to machine learning experts and leading social science researchers using LLMs.
      </p>

      <h2>Details</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Dates:</strong> September 22–26, 2025<br />
        <strong>Location:</strong> Nuffield College, University of Oxford<br />
        <strong>Cost:</strong> Fully funded — no registration fee<br />
        <strong>Application deadline:</strong> TBA (applications open April 10)
      </p>

      <h2>How to Apply</h2>
      <p>
        <!-- Phase 2: Replace with embedded application form -->
        The application form will be available here from April 10.
        In the meantime, for questions about the application process, contact
        <a href="mailto:maksim.zubok@nuffield.ox.ac.uk">maksim.zubok@nuffield.ox.ac.uk</a>.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <p>
        <a href="/summer-school/2025/" class="btn btn--outline">View the 2025 programme →</a>
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</Base>
